  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (028e888 2022-07-30T00:03:45.078239085Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge install\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThere are no staged files but forge install does not agree. Should it care about untracked files? If so, should the message it emits be different?\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ forge install https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts\r\nInstalling openzeppelin-contracts in \"/somedir/lib/openzeppelin-contracts\" (url: Some(\"https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts\"), tag: None)\r\nError:\r\nThere are changes in your working/staging area. Commit them first or add the `--no-commit` option.\r\n$ git status\r\nOn branch master\r\nUntracked files:\r\n   (use \"git add <file>...\" to include in what will be committed)\r\n   ...various untracked files...\r\n\r\nnothing added to commit but untracked files present (use \"git add\" to track)\r\n```\r\n",
