    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Fair enough yes, \"working/\" is included in the message. Frankly, I thought that's probably an imprecise warning string in Foundry rather than believing its literal meaning that something about forge's \"commit\" behavior would care about un-staged un-tracked files in the working dirs. I.e., those are not really \"changes\" (vs potential new additions etc).\r\n\r\nPerhaps a rewording of the message is warranted?\r\n\r\n\"This command requires clean working and staging areas, including no untracked files. Modify .gitignore and/or add/commit  first, or add the `--no-commit` option.\"",
